-- Cromwell to Raise $105 Million to Buy Qantas Headquarters, Review Says
-- Nichola Saminather
-- 2010-07-12T21:42:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/cromwell-to-raise-105-million-to-buy-qantas-headquarters-review-says.html

          
          
             Cromwell Group is seeking to raise
as much as A$120 million to buy Qantas Airways Ltd.’s global
headquarters in Sydney, the Australian Financial Review
reported. The company yesterday said it would try to raise as
much as A$80 million at 75 Australian cents a share, and between
A$40 million and A$68 million through a rights issue at 72
Australian cents, according to the report. Redefine, South
Africa’s largest real estate investment trust, will put in A$52
llion and participate in the rights issue, bringing its stake in
Cromwell to 19.9 percent, the newspaper said.  
